coming from the 3d and rendering side i feel like you could improve a lot by looking into your composition and lighting. also due to the mc textures theres just inherently going to be lots of stuff happening so be sure to get a composition and framing that clearly focuses on the subject, from there you can enhance it and make it stand out with lighting so make it pop from the bg with some rim lights, some colored fills for contrast. you can really guide the viewer that way

out of those 4 the last one i feel like is the best in terms of the whole lighting and composition thing. clear subject, the face, placed somewhere according to the rule of thirds with intentional lighting that doesnt distract from anything and making the subject stand out from the obviously darker background
